ls -a 
will list all the content inside this directory
rm -rf .git // will remove the git in the react client app.
move the gitignore file into the root
remove the node_modules and replace with 
node_modules
node_modules/
this is to track the node modules both in the client and server.
add .env as well in the git ignore
cd to the root then init git there.

we make use of rafce to generate our react arrow function component export

React Bootstrap:
https://react-bootstrap.github.io/   // npm i react-bootstrap

Bootswatch:
https://bootswatch.com/

We download the min.css we want to use from the link above (https://bootswatch.com/) and paste
inside the src folder. Then import it in index.js. Go into the client and run
npm i react-bootstrap

